    <main>
      <section id="problem">
        <h2>The System Is a Trauma Engine</h2>
        <div class="duo">
          <div>
            <p class="lede">
              The institutions meant to neutralize conflict are now primary manufacturers of it. In too many family court ecosystems, adversarial processes amplify harm and entrench trauma pathways.
            </p>
            <div class="quote">
              Our current model doesn’t just fail to heal—it generates new wounds and encodes them into the lives of children who never chose the battlefield.
            </div>
            <p>
              Children are leveraged as procedural assets in zero-sum contests. Psychological safety is rarely the central metric. We are witnessing an archaic operating system still optimized for positional victory rather than relational integrity.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is not inevitable—it's a design failure. Design can be re-authored. Outcomes can be re-oriented. Metrics can be re-centered on child well-being and long-term developmental resilience.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="label">Paradigm Shift</div>
              <h3>Reframing the Core Question</h3>
              <p>
                Instead of asking: Who is right? We begin asking: What relational architecture minimizes harm and maximizes the child's long-term flourishing?
              </p>
              <ul class="pillars-list">
                <li><strong>Shift the locus:</strong> From adversarial position to shared developmental stewardship.</li>
                <li><strong>Shift the unit:</strong> From isolated litigants to a multi-perspective care system.</li>
                <li><strong>Shift the metric:</strong> From procedural completion to measurable child resilience.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <details>
              <summary>Why adversarial models persist</summary>
              <p>
                Legacy incentives, informational asymmetry, cultural habituation, and absence of outcome transparency reinforce a failing pattern. Without new tooling that makes alternative pathways measurable and respected, system inertia dominates.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="manifesto">
        <h2>The MediAI Manifesto</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          We assert that technology must not accelerate extraction or amplify bias; it must extend human conscience, deepen mutual comprehension, and architect pathways toward humane resolution.
        </p>

        <h3>Pillars of the New Paradigm</h3>
        <ul class="pillars-list">
          <li><strong>Child-Centricity:</strong> The child's psychological and emotional safety is the invariant anchor and terminal metric.</li>
          <li><strong>Radical Transparency:</strong> No black-box influence on life-altering outcomes—explainability is governance.</li>
          <li><strong>Proactive Ethical Guardrails:</strong> Safety and anti-bias are generative design primitives, not retrofitted patches.</li>
          <li><strong>Empathic Design:</strong> Interfaces and models engineered to de-escalate, surface shared values, and preserve dignity.</li>
          <li><strong>Regenerative Data Stewardship:</strong> Data as entrusted commons—used only to remediate harm patterns and uplift collective well-being.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top:2.6rem;">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="label">Reorientation</div>
            <h3>From Velocity to Wisdom</h3>
            <p>We resist purely efficiency-centric optimization. Speed without ethical depth accelerates damage.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="label">Ethics</div>
            <h3>Embedded Guardrails</h3>
            <p>Risk modeling, bias audits, and accountability scaffolds are integral system layers, not optional add-ons.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="label">Humanity</div>
            <h3>Designing for Dignity</h3>
            <p>Interfaces that function as emotional regulators reduce escalation loops and reinforce relational agency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="congress-ask">
        <h2>The 5-Minute Congress Ask</h2>
        <p class="lede">A strategic blueprint: three fiscally grounded and ethically urgent pathways for national adoption of restorative, child-centric resolution ecosystems.</p>
        <details open>
          <summary>1. The Children's Compassionate Resolution Fund ($25M)</summary>
          <p>
            Competitive grants within HHS to pilot non-adversarial, AI-assisted mediation frameworks. Core KPI: empirically measured improvements in child well-being—not just docket throughput.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>2. National Task Force on Ethical AI in Family Adjudication</summary>
          <p>
            A multidisciplinary consortium (jurists, child psychologists, AI ethicists, trauma-focused legal scholars) to define binding transparency, safety, and auditability standards before widespread deployment.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>3. "Best Interests of the Child" Data Initiative</summary>
            <p>
              NIH-led longitudinal comparative data infrastructure: adversarial outcomes versus restorative alternatives. Moves decision-making from anecdote to evidence.
            </p>
        </details>
        <div class="accented">
          <strong>Framing:</strong> These asks are architecturally conservative: they conserve family integrity, child mental health capital, and public trust in justice systems while reducing long-horizon social costs.
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="medi-ai">
        <h2>MediAI: Adaptive Mediation Vector</h2>
        <div class="duo">
          <div>
            <p class="lede">
              MediAI is not a judge. It is a regulated, ethically-specified co-pilot facilitating de-escalation, alignment discovery, and child-vocalized outcome modeling under strict transparency.
            </p>
            <h3>Functional Core</h3>
            <ul class="pillars-list">
              <li><strong>Real-time Emotional De-escalation:</strong> Suggests reframes for escalatory language while preserving semantic intent.</li>
              <li><strong>Value Convergence Mapping:</strong> Identifies overlapping priorities hidden beneath adversarial postures.</li>
              <li><strong>Scenario Visualization:</strong> Projects multi-outcome pathways with annotated impact vectors on child well-being metrics.</li>
              <li><strong>Ethical Child Voice Representation:</strong> Integrates developmental psych frameworks to prevent proxy distortion.</li>
              <li><strong>Adaptive Protocol Guidance:</strong> Nudges participants toward restorative sequence patterns validated in pilots.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="label">Integrity Layers</div>
              <h3>Governance Stack</h3>
              <p style="margin-bottom:.7rem;"><strong>Layer 1:</strong> Transparent Model Cards + provenance tracking.</p>
              <p style="margin-bottom:.7rem;"><strong>Layer 2:</strong> Continuous bias sentinel with threshold interrupts.</p>
              <p style="margin-bottom:.7rem;"><strong>Layer 3:</strong> Human-in-the-loop escalation failsafe protocol.</p>
              <p style="margin-bottom:.7rem;"><strong>Layer 4:</strong> Immutable audit log (privacy-preserving hashing) for regulatory inspection.</p>
              <p><strong>Layer 5:</strong> Regenerative feedback assimilation—harm signals route directly into model governance queue.</p>
            </div>
            <details>
              <summary>Why a "Vector" not a "Platform"</summary>
              <p>
                A vector integrates into existing process lanes with minimal structural disruption, enabling incremental transformation and comparative data collection without demanding wholesale procedural replacement on day one.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

